</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8DC56D0E28831D97D2484FD179073B13" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" type="note">
<paragraph id="D0ADC942BD09AA1BCB4DCCEEC8598DD9" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2FFF80E214BB8DD130FD9F298675DBD0" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName id="23288A6C33D12988959CECF579346761" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="simmonsii">
<emphasis id="318F9D44166294C54E28D9813360DBC3" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">Scapania simmonsii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms an isolated lineage within 
<taxonomicName id="5C7C412F95E770123B72DD09C400F483" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0A22C1B17142CB6E6FD8D4618C572305" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">S.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subg. 
<taxonomicName id="26B6DAE7D100BDDC811413594AB7180A" authorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="sect. Simmonsia (R. M. Schust.) Vana, Hentschel, Joch. Muell. &amp; Heinrichs" baseAuthorityYear="2012" class="Hepaticae" family="Scapaniaceae" genus="Scapania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17C6708DDC850CCAA9ACEAEA2BFA7518" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="14">Scapania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, hence, we erect a section for this species rather than using subsectional rank (
<bibRefCitation id="AA3C94D5E62F229078408B76D91DB4A6" author="Schuster, RM" journalOrPublisher="Annales Botanici Fennici" pageId="1" pageNumber="14" refId="B4" refString="Schuster, RM, 1974. The Hepaticae and Anthocerotae of North America. Columbia University Press, New York." title="The Hepaticae and Anthocerotae of North America. Columbia University Press, New York." year="1974">Schuster 1974</bibRefCitation>
). Distinctive features of the monotypic section are the deflexed-involute, broad, concave ventral leaf lobes that stand away from the stem at almost right angles and leaf cell walls with very large, nodulose trigones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
